			<description><![CDATA[<p>AdMeld is looking for Client Services Account Managers to manage our relationships with the world's leading web publishers. The positions are full time, mid-level and based in the company's NYC and London offices, respectively. This is a great opportunity to join a company defining a new space in the online advertising industry.<br /> <br /> The Account Management team is responsible for servicing all aspects of clients' accounts from implementation to optimization and all ongoing concerns. The Account Manager will play a critical role in driving overall client satisfaction and therefore the general success of the business. <br /><br /> <strong>Key Responsibilities: </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Enable our publisher customers to maximize their       revenue achieved using the AdMeld product</li>
<li>Oversee the AdMeld implementation process, from       kick-off through launch</li>
<li>Train clients on the AdMeld product and client facing       tools</li>
<li>Responsible for       sourcing and negotiating deals with ad networks for the web's leading       brands. </li>
<li>Proactively manage assigned client's ad network portfolio, making recommendations for changes and seeking out new opportunities for improvement</li>
<li>Compile performance evaluations for each client,       highlighting the value AdMeld adds</li>
<li>Serve as clients' primary contact, providing them with       insight and advice regarding every aspect of their account</li>
<li>Ensure the satisfactory resolution of all support       requests, including network ad display and data issues</li>
<li>Provide ideas and feedback about how to improve the       AdMeld products and services for our customers</li>
</ul>
<p><br /><br /> <strong>Required Skills and Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Outstanding written and verbal communication skills, being capable of conveying an issue clearly, making points concisely and ensuring all sides understand each other</li>
<li>Publisher / ad       network negotiations. </li>
<li>Prior client management experience, especially with web       publishers </li>
</ul>
<ul type="disc">
<li>Project management or account management skills, specifically, being able to lay out deliverables and follow-through on hitting them</li>
<li>Strong troubleshooting skills with ability to analyze the components of an ad related problem and get to its root, as well as providing necessary suggestions for resolution</li>
<li>Passion and desire to play a key role in driving this       new business to success in the online advertising technology space</li>
<li>High level of initiative to get resolution and drive improvements       to the business</li>
</ul>
<ul type="disc">
<li>Deep understanding of the online advertising industry, preferably       from the perspective of a publisher or ad network</li>
<li>Proficiency in Excel and PowerPoint</li>
<li>A Bachelor's degree and at least 4 years work       experience</li>
</ul>
<p><br /> <strong>The following are all plusses: </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Familiarity with HTML, jscript and ad tag structures </li>
<li>Experience working with ad servers</li>
</ul>
<ul type="disc">
<li>Statistical modeling skills</li>
<li>Understanding of SQL</li>
<li>An MBA</li>
</ul>]]></description>
